# To turn over soil with a spade to loosen the ground for planting.

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|en|spader}}

===Etymology 2===
Probably from {{bor|en|it|spade}}, plural of {{m|it|spada|t=the ace of spades|lit=sword, spade}}, from earlier ''*spata'', from {{der|en|la|spatha}}, from {{der|en|grc|σπᾰ́θη}}. Cognate with Etymology 1. So called for the shape, though what the shape was exactly meant to represent has been debated.<ref>{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary|pos=n.2|noformat=1|v=23943}}</ref>

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|card games}} A [[playing card]] marked with the symbol {{m|mul|♠}}.
#: {{ux|en|I've got only one '''spade''' in my hand.}}
# {{lb|en|offensive|ethnic slur}} A [[black]] person.
#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Wallace Thurman|title={{w|The Blacker the Berry (novel)|The Blacker the Berry}}|year=1929|year_published=1970|publisher=Collier Books|location=New York|page=161|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/blackerberrynove00thur/page/161/mode/1up|isbn=978-0-02-054750-1|passage=And as for a divorce, I know plenty '''spades''' right here in Harlem get married any time they want to.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1968|title=w:Slouching Towards Bethlehem|chapter=Slouching Towards Bethlehem|author=w:Joan Didion|passage=Example: Max was in a hospital in New York and "the night nurse was a groovy '''spade''', and in the afternoon for therapy there was a chick from Israel who was interesting, but there was nothing much to do in the morning, so I left".}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Tom Wolfe|title=w:The Electric Kool-Aid Acid Test|year=1968|year_published=1997|page=9|publisher=Bantam|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/electrickoolaida00wolf_0/page/9/mode/1up|isbn=978-0-553-26491-3|passage=It had even gotten to the point that Negroes were no longer in the hip scene, not even as totem figures. It was unbelievable. '''''Spades''''', the very soul figures of Hip, of jazz, of the hip vocabulary itself, man and like dig and baby and scarf and split and later and so fine, of civil rights and graduating from Reed College and living on North Beach, down Mason, and balling '''spade''' cats—all that good elaborate petting and patting and pouring soul all over the '''spades'''—all over, finished, incredibly.}}

