==Swedish==
{{wp|sv:}}
[[File:Shovel leaning against a wall.jpg|thumb|en spade]]
[[File:Buket and spade on Killahoey Strand - geograph.org.uk - 1426946.jpg|thumb|{{l|sv|hink}} och '''spade''' <nowiki>[</nowiki>[[bucket and spade|bucket and '''spade''']]<nowiki>]</nowiki>]]

===Etymology===
From {{der|sv|non|spaði}}, from {{der|sv|gml|spade}}, from {{der|sv|gem-pro|*spadô}}.

===Noun===
{{sv-noun|c}}

# a [[shovel]] (for digging – compare {{m|sv|skyffel}})
# a {{l|en|spade}} (garden tool, or toy spade or the like)
# {{lb|sv|chiefly in compounds}} any of various spade-like tools

====Usage notes====
Common, everyday word, and the first word native speakers are likely to think of when translating {{m+|en|shovel}}. More common compared to ''spade'' in English.

